  "body": "### Description\n\nquarkus-oidc currently enforces iat as mandatory claim and there is no way to make it as optional:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/main/extensions/oidc/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/oidc/runtime/OidcProvider.java#L212\r\n\r\n\r\nWe use quarkus-oidc to support multi tenancy for our tokens, but as they do not have the iat claim present, the parsing fails with the following error:\r\n`rejected due to invalid claims or other invalid content. Additional details: [[3] No Issued At (iat) claim present.]`\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nI would recommend making the iat claim optional via configuration properties (just like the exp claim for example):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/main/extensions/oidc/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/oidc/runtime/OidcProvider.java#L201-L203",
